## Why This Is Asked
This question probes practical design of multilingual, budget-aware Azure AI pipelines with safety and observability in a real-world support scenario.

## Key Concepts
- Multilingual real-time translation
- PII redaction and data safety guardrails
- Tenant-specific policy via Key Vault classifications
- Token budget gating and fallback UX
- Grounding on a versioned KB with Cognitive Search
- Drift detection and retraining via Azure Monitor

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo: redaction + budget gate
function prepareQuery(input, tenantId) {
  const redacted = redactPII(input);
  const translated = translate(redacted, 'en');
  const budget = getTenantBudget(tenantId);
  if (wouldExceedBudget(budget, estimatedTokens(translated))) {
    return { fallback: true, type: 'diagnostic' };
  }
  return { query: translated, tenantId };
}
```

